                    The Ambassador in China (
                        Hurley
                    ) to the President and the
                        Secretary of State
                    The source copy does not indicate whether this
                        message was sent via Army or Navy channels.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv02</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1247</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1247</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-25T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-25T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="1247" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1247">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Nanking Embassy Files: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1247<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HMGPJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss> and the
                        Secretary of State</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1247fn1">The source copy does not indicate whether this
                        message was sent via Army or Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-25">25 July
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(The following message is top secret and urgent for the eyes alone of the
                    Secretary of State, <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">James F. Byrnes</persName>,
                    Potsdam, Germany, for the President from Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_HMGPJ1">Hurley</persName>.)</p>
                <p>Your message White House Number 311<note n="2" xml:id="d1247fn2">
                        <ref target="#d1246">Document No. 1246</ref>.</note> delivered to Prime
                    Minister <persName corresp="#p_STV1">Soong</persName> at his residence at 2130
                        hours,<note n="3" xml:id="d1247fn3">i. e., 9:30 p.m.</note> Chungking time,
                    July 25th. Generalissimo out of Chungking across Yangtze River in mountains. We
                    intend to complete translation and deliver message to him tonight.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
